      <li class="form-line" data-type="control_text" id="id_156">

        <div id="cid_156" class="form-input-wide">

          <div id="text_156" class="form-html" data-component="text">

            <p>Preferred share class A are invested in all kinds of portfolio of SEDPI. The historical dividend rate in the past five years is 3%-6% per annum. Price per share is PhP5,000. </p>

            <p><strong>Preferred share class B </strong>are invested in debt instruments to microfinance institutions. Dividend rate is projected to be 4%-7% per annum. Price per share is PhP10,000.</p>

            <p><strong>Preferred share class C</strong> are invested in equity instruments to microfinance institutions. Dividend rate is projected to be 5%-9% per annum. Price per share is PhP100,000.</p>

            <p><strong>Preferred share class D</strong> are invested in social enterprises in the agricultural sector. Dividend rate is projected to be 5%-10% per annum. Price per share is PhP50,000.</p>

            <p><strong>Preferred share class E</strong> are invested in real estate properties. Dividend rate is projected to be 8%-12% per annum. Price per share is PhP250,000.</p>

            <p><strong>Organic Options, Inc. (OOI)</strong> is a marketing company for organic produce. SEDPI extends loans to OOI. Interest rate for investors is 12% per annum, fixed. Minimum investment is PhP10,000. <a href="https://vincerapisura.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ooi-background-information-190618.pdf" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Download partner's appraisal report.</a></p>

            <p><strong>Alalay sa Kaunlaran, Inc. (ASKI)</strong> is a microfinance NGO that provides financial services to low income groups in Central and Northern Luzon. SEDPI extends loans to ASKI. Interest rate for investors is 9% per annum, fixed. Minimum investment is PhP10,000. <a href="https://vincerapisura.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/aski-background-information-190719.pdf" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Download partner's appraisal report.</a></p>

            <p><strong>Pantukan Chess Club Cooperative (PCCC)</strong> is a cooperative that provides financial services to low income groups in Compostella Valley. SEDPI extends loans to PCCC. Interest rate for investors is 8% per annum, fixed. Minimum investment is PhP10,000.</p>

            <p><strong>United Sugar Planters Cooperative (USPD)</strong> is a cooperative that provides financial services to low income groups in Davao del Sur. SEDPI extends loans to USPD. Interest rate for investors is 9% per annum, fixed. Minimum investment is PhP10,000.</p>

            <p><strong>Tagum Coop (TC)</strong> is a cooperative that provides financial services to low income groups mostly in Mindanao with headquarters in Davao del Norte. SEDPI places share capital in Tagum Coop. Dividend rate for investors is 7-10% per annum, variable. Minimum investment is PhP10,000.</p>

          </div>

